:74:\"Agrapart & Fils | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:225:\"Located in the heart of the Côte des Blancs, Agrapart & Fils was founded in Avize by Arthur Agrapart at the end of the 19th century. Today, it is widely considered to be one of the finest grower-produced Champagnes produced.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"24\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:44;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"Veuve Cliquot | Effervescence - A Champange & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:188:\"The iconic yellow label of Veuve Clicquot needs no introduction.  From entry-level blends to vintage wines to prestige cuvées, the Clicquot portfolio offers quality at every price point.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"19\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:16;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"André Clouet | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:286:\"André Clouet’s 20 acres of Grand Cru vineyards are situated in the coveted middle slopes of Ambonnay and Bouzy. They make a full range of Champagnes, including most famously the glorious Cuvée 1911, which is comprised of 100% Pinot Noir from Clouet’s ten best lieux-dits in Bouzy.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"19\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:47;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:75:\"Billecart-Salmon | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:172:\"We are honored to celebrate the 200 year anniversary of Billecart-Salmon, a remarkable family-owned house whose motto is \"to privilege quality, to strive for excellence.”\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"30\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:48;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:68:\"Bollinger | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:254:\"Champagne Bollinger has created prestigious wines with character, distinguished by their elegance and complexity, since 1829. These outstanding Champagnes are the result of rigorous attention to detail, for Bollinger accepts nothing less than excellence.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:49;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:74:\"De Sousa & Fils | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:245:\"De Sousa Winery has been devoted to authenticity and quality since its inception. Their cultivation of older vines, use of organic fertilizer, and respect for the terroir have produced exceptional quality wines of extraordinary value since 1986.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"13\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:50;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:68:\"Delamotte | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:318:\"Delamotte was founded in Reims in 1760 by François Delamotte, a vineyard owner. The houses have been under the direction of Didier Depond in Le Mesnil-sur-Oger since 1988. The wine should be – from the very start – subtle, profound, rich with the aromas and flavors which ultimately create outstanding Champagne.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:51;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"Dom Pérignon | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:263:\"Lovers of legendary Champagne need no introduction to Dom Pérignon, the prestige cuvée of powerhouse Moët & Chandon.  Made only in extraordinary years, Dom Pérignon is always a vintage-designate tête de cuvée wine that is designed for extraordinary ageing.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"30\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:52;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:69:\"Eric Rodez | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:235:\"The estate of Champagne Rodez is located in the Grand Cru that is Ambonnay, the heart of Pinot Noir country, and spans an area of 6.12 hectares. The Rodez family has been making wine for nine generations, beginning as far back as 1757.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"24\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:53;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"Guiborat Fils | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:304:\"The Fouquet family has farmed small parcels in Cramant, Champagne since 1885. Champagne Guiborat Fils overall production is tiny, as grapes from five of their eight hectares are regularly sold to the Champagne house of Laurent-Perrier. Farming is all done by hand, with aggressive pruning and low yields.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"30\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:54;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"Huré Frères | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:227:\"Champagne Huré-Fréres was started just over 50 years ago and is still very much a family business. Today Raoul Huré and his two sons, Francois and Pierre invite you to discover their maison at Ludes in the Montagne de Reims.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"19\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:55;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:69:\"Jacquesson | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:221:\"Jacquesson is one of Champagne’s most venerable houses. As Champagne lovers have the chance to experience more and more of Jacquesson’s new releases, the genius of this house’s ideas is coming more fully into focus.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:56;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:63:\"Krug | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:193:\"Effervescence, May 3-5 in Los Angeles. Behind every precious drop of Krug stands the dream of a visionary. One man who, long before others, understood that the essence of Champagne is pleasure.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:57;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:65:\"Lanson | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:281:\"The House of Lanson was founded in 1760 by François Delamotte, an influential character in Reims society. The joint owner, alongside his wife, of a not-insubstantial vineyard in Cumières and Ay, he decided to found his own Champagne house – one of the very first ever to exist.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:58;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"Marc Hébrart | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:231:\"Marc Hébrart Champagne has been in production since 1964 and a member of the Special Club since 1985. Hébrart farms 14 hectares of vines on 65 different sites in 6 villages, including premier cru vineyards and grand cru villages.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"30\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:59;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"Marion Bosser | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:271:\"It is in Hautvillers, a world UNESCO heritage site and the famous village where monk Dom Pérignon made his auspicious discovery, that we find the rising house of Marion-Bosser. This is an extraordinary Champagne to watch as it is rediscovered on the international scene.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"29\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:60;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:74:\"Moët & Chandon | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:267:\"Synonymous with luxury, the wines of Moët & Chandon epitomize the region of Champagne.  From entry-level bubblies made with passion and precision to rarities that grace the cellars of collectors around the world, Moët & Chandon is one of the icons of the industry.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"24\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:61;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:71:\"Moussé Fils | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:237:\"A grower since 1750, Champagne Moussé sits in the village of Cuisles, in a valley perpendicular to the Vallée de la Marne. While pinot meunier often struggles to be taken seriously in Champagne, at Moussé, pinot meunier is celebrated.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"24\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:62;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:71:\"Philipponnat | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:263:\"Philipponnat is one of the last Champagne houses to be run by a member of its founding family. Through great vision, technical skill and perfectionist attention to detail, Philipponnat is gaining reverence for its entire portfolio of richly expressive Champagnes.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:63;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:73:\"Pierre Péters | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:309:\"The Pierre Péters estate, situated in the heart of the \"Côte des Blancs\" in the village of Le Mesnil sur Oger, has been a family house for six generations and has produced Grand Cru Blanc de Blancs Champagnes since 1919. As a Champagne grower-producer, their wines come exclusively from their own vineyards.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"30\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:64;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:72:\"R. H. Coutier | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:297:\"Champagne R. H. Coutier is located in the grand cru village of Ambonnay, one of the top wine-producing towns on the Montagne de Reims. The Coutiers’ vineyards are planted with one-third chardonnay and two-thirds pinot noir. Champagne R. H. Coutier only produces 25,000 bottles in any given year.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"24\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:65;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:73:\"Pierre Moncuit | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:234:\"Located in Mesnil sur Oger, in the heart of the Côte des Blancs, Champagne Pierre Moncuit, a family house and a grower-producer, has based its reputation on a continual search for quality while maintaining its respect for traditions.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"30\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:66;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:66:\"Ruinart | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:297:\"Ruinart is the oldest established Champagne house and has been exclusively producing Champagne since 1729. The house is today proudly represented within LVMH’s luxury portfolio. The legendary monk Dom Ruinart and his extraordinary history are revived to take their place on the world wine stage.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:67;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:74:\"Vilmart et Cie. | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:295:\"Vilmart & Cie. traces its history back to 1890. From the beginning, Vilmart & Cie. has always been a “récoltant-manipulant,” making Champagne exclusively from estate-owned vines. Beloved by sommeliers and made in tiny coveted quantities, the wines of Vilmart & Cie are simply extraordinary.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"13\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:68;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:68:\"Gusbourne | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:267:\"The original Gusbourne Estate in the United Kingdom dates back to 1410. In 2004, Andrew Weeber took over the estate with a clear vision and a single goal: to create English sparkling wines that would stand up alongside the very finest offerings from across the globe.\";s:13:\"wpseo_linkdex\";s:2:\"35\";s:19:\"wpseo_content_score\";s:2:\"30\";}i:69;a:4:{s:11:\"wpseo_title\";s:68:\"Pere Mata | Effervescence - A Champagne & Sparkling Wine Celebration\";s:10:\"wpseo_desc\";s:320:\"The Cava made by winemaker Pere Mata under the Mata Coloma winery banner has redefined the entire Spanish sparkling wine industry, p