_2_sponsors_9_website','field_5a6a52cbf0262'),(1780,45,'question_list_2_subhead','Media'),(1781,45,'_question_list_2_subhead','field_5a6a160b58e67'),(1782,45,'question_list_2_list_0_question','Are there press passes available for Effervescence?'),(1783,45,'_question_list_2_list_0_question','field_5a6a163c58e69'),(1784,45,'question_list_2_list_0_answer','Thank you for your interest in Effervescence! Please submit media inquiries and requests for information using our <a href=\"https://effervescencela.com/contact/\">contact form</a>.'),(1785,45,'_question_list_2_list_0_answer','field_5a6a164158e6a'),(1790,45,'question_list_2_list','2'),(1791,45,'_question_list_2_list','field_5a6a162458e68'),(1920,228,'_edit_lock','1525650180:4'),(1921,228,'_edit_last','4'),(1922,228,'event_type','4'),(1923,228,'_event_type','field_5a621223b7bc7'),(1924,228,'event_excerpt','Swedish Champagne expert Richard Juhlin, in a rare US appearance, will conduct a master class on how mature Champagne evolves through the years.\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.'),(1925,228,'_event_excerpt','field_5a621b80bbd03'),(1926,228,'event_content','We are deeply honored to host expert author Richard Juhlin, widely considered to be the foremost Champagne connoisseur in the world. Juhlin has published extensively on Champagne and is reputed to have tasted more of it than anyone else over the course of his long and varied career. From James Beard awards to France’s Legion d’Honneur, Juhlin is particularly revered for his blind-tasting abilities and encyclopedic knowledge of the region.\r\n\r\nFor this Master Class, Juhlin will guide us as we examine - and taste - how Champagne ages and matures through four decades - 1970, 1980, 1990 and 2000. We\'ll be treated to rarities not commonly available as we explore both youthful and aged examples of the region\'s very best bottlings.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>How do both terroir and chemistry impact an aging bottle?</h3>\r\n&nbsp;</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Some of the topics covered during this unique master class: </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">What is the golden age for Champagne at the moment?</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Have production methods changed over the decades, and how does this reflect the style today?</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Does the feeling of terroir change with maturity?</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The concept of Œnothèque &amp; Vinothèque</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 2009\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 2006\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 2000 P2\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 1996 P2\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 1988 P3\r\n\r\nTaittinger Vintage 1976'),(1927,228,'_event_content','field_5a621095d626c'),(1928,228,'event_package',''),(1929,228,'_event_package','field_5a6222a9f43c7'),(1930,228,'event_passes','1'),(1931,228,'_event_passes','field_5a625f5e1c1fe'),(1932,228,'event_venue','114'),(1933,228,'_event_venue','field_5a6224a7dde1d'),(1934,228,'event_start_date','20180504'),(1935,228,'_event_start_date','field_5a622aacf8cf9'),(1936,228,'event_start_time','10:30:00'),(1937,228,'_event_start_time','field_5a622acff8cfa'),(1938,228,'event_end_time',''),(1939,228,'_event_end_time','field_5a622b05f8cfb'),(1940,228,'event_participant_groups','1'),(1941,228,'_event_participant_groups','field_5a6224cad31dc'),(1942,228,'event_banner','450'),(1943,228,'_event_banner','field_5a6260de00b05'),(1944,228,'event_sidebar_image','131'),(1945,228,'_event_sidebar_image','field_5a6260fa00b06'),(1946,228,'event_thumbnail','456'),(1947,228,'_event_thumbnail','field_5a69fb1602917'),(1948,228,'event_options_event_hide_guide_btn','1'),(1949,228,'_event_options_eve