ert author Richard Juhlin, widely considered to be the foremost Champagne connoisseur in the world. Juhlin has published extensively on Champagne, and is reputed to have tasted more of it than anyone else over the course of his long and varied career. From James Beard awards to France’s Legion d’Honneur, Juhlin is particularly revered for his blind-tasting abilities and encyclopedic knowledge of the region. For this Master Class, we will examine five decades of Champagne. Juhlin will guide us as we examine the evolution of great Champagne over time. How do both terroir and chemistry impact an aging bottle? We’ll be treated to rarities not commonly available as we explore both youthful and aged examples of the region’s very best bottlings.'),(2354,247,'_event_content','field_5a621095d626c'),(2355,247,'event_package','a:1:{i:0;s:1:\"7\";}'),(2356,247,'_event_package','field_5a6222a9f43c7'),(2357,247,'event_passes_0_title','Master Class III: \"Five Decades of Champagne\"'),(2358,247,'_event_passes_0_title','field_5a625f711c1ff'),(2359,247,'event_passes_0_price','$300.00'),(2360,247,'_event_passes_0_price','field_5a625fa91c200'),(2361,247,'event_passes_0_description','Expert author Richard Juhlin guides us as we examine the evolution of great Champagne over time.'),(2362,247,'_event_passes_0_description','field_5a625fc61c201'),(2363,247,'event_passes','1'),(2364,247,'_event_passes','field_5a625f5e1c1fe'),(2365,247,'event_venue','8'),(2366,247,'_event_venue','field_5a6224a7dde1d'),(2367,247,'event_start_date','20180504'),(2368,247,'_event_start_date','field_5a622aacf8cf9'),(2369,247,'event_start_time',''),(2370,247,'_event_start_time','field_5a622acff8cfa'),(2371,247,'event_end_time',''),(2372,247,'_event_end_time','field_5a622b05f8cfb'),(2373,247,'event_participant_groups_0_header','Speaker'),(2374,247,'_event_participant_groups_0_header','field_5a6224e6d31dd'),(2375,247,'event_participant_groups_0_participants','combo'),(2376,247,'_event_participant_groups_0_participan