s'),(43016,2101,'_event_passes_0_title','field_5a625f711c1ff'),(43017,2101,'event_passes_0_price','$875'),(43018,2101,'_event_passes_0_price','field_5a625fa91c200'),(43019,2101,'event_passes_0_description',''),(43020,2101,'_event_passes_0_description','field_5a625fc61c201'),(43021,2103,'event_type','4'),(43022,2103,'_event_type','field_5a621223b7bc7'),(43023,2103,'event_excerpt','Experience the beauty of our world through a glass of champagne with Richard Juhlin, author of <i>The Scent of Champagne</i>. A master class on how our environment influences our perception of Champagne!\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.'),(43024,2103,'_event_excerpt','field_5a621b80bbd03'),(43025,2103,'event_content','\"Champagne is the only wine that can accommodate all of nature\'s fragrances in a single glass. Its unsurpassed aromatic diversity makes it possible to pick up all types of nature and fragrances and create harmony with the environment. By virtue of the character and fragrance of the location, different aspects of the Champagne\'s personality will be highlighted and reinforced. This is the heart of the matter, and the reason why I do not devote myself to Wine Hiking but instead created the concept of <em>Champagne Hiking</em>\"\r\n\r\n<em>Richard Juhlin</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRichard Juhlin’s most recent book, <em><a href=\"https://champagnehiking.tictail.com\">Champagne Hiking</a>,</em> offers a compelling examination of how Champagne is experienced differently by consuming it in different locations. Does the environment in which we open a bottle impact our sensory perception of it? Does bubbly taste better at higher altitudes? Juhlin will explore the science behind the phenomenon as the nature of Champagne interacts with Mother Nature – expect the unexpected at this tasting!\r\n\r\nSome of the topics covered during this unique master class:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The environmental impact on the drinking experience</li>\r\n 	<li>Why Champagne tastes the best at a particular time, in a particular place</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nAubry \'Le Nombre d\'Or\' Brut NV\r\nAndré Clouet Millesime 2008\r\nDe Sousa Blanc de Blancs Reserve Grand Cru NV\r\nMarc Hebrart \'Selection\' Brut NV\r\nLouis Roederer Brut Rose 2010\r\nBollinger\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1863\" src=\"https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Book-Notebook-in-Wooden-Case-2-800x655.png\" alt=\"Champagne Hiking Book\" width=\"800\" height=\"655\" />\r\n\r\nTo place an order on <i>Champagne Hiking</i> online, please visit the Champagne Hiking Store <a href=\"https://champagnehiking.tictail.com\">here</a>.'),(43026,2103,'_event_content','field_5a621095d626c'),(43027,2103,'event_package',''),(43028,2103,'_event_package','field_5a6222a9f43c7'),(43029,2103,'event_passes_0_title','Master Class Pass'),(43030,2103,'_event_passes_0_title','field_5a625f711c1ff'),(43031,2103,'event_passes_0_price','$100'),(43032,2103,'_event_passes_0_price','field_5a625fa91c200'),(43033,2103,'event_passes_0_description',''),(43034,2103,'_event_passes_0_description','field_5a625fc61c201'),(43035,2103,'event_passes','1'),(43036,2103,'_event_passes','field_5a625f5e1c1fe'),(43037,2103,'event_venue','114'),(43038,2103,'_event_venue','field_5a6224a7dde1d'),(43039,2103,'event_start_date','20180505'),(43040,2103,'_event_start_date','field_5a622aacf8cf9'),(43041,2103,'event_start_time','10:30:00'),(43042,2103,'_event_start_time','field_5a622acff8cfa'),(43043,2103,'event_end_time',''),(43044,2103,'_event_end_time','field_5a622b05f8cfb'),(43045,2103,'event_participant_groups_0_header','Speaker'),(43046,2103,'_event_participant_groups_0_header','field_5a6224e6d31dd'),(43047,2103,'event_participant_groups_0_pa