ups_0_producers','field_5a622caadb3a8'),(43335,2113,'event_options_event_sign_up_mode','0'),(43336,2113,'_event_options_event_sign_up_mode','field_5a8f3682d5fb5'),(43337,2113,'event_sold_out','1'),(43338,2113,'_event_sold_out','field_5a9842247846b'),(43393,2117,'event_type','4'),(43394,2117,'_event_type','field_5a621223b7bc7'),(43395,2117,'event_excerpt','Master Sommelier Geoff Kruth on the role of big Champagne houses in the modern market.\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.'),(43396,2117,'_event_excerpt','field_5a621b80bbd03'),(43397,2117,'event_content','Join Master Sommelier and noted wine educator Geoff Kruth for this comprehensive exploration and tasting of Champagnes from the finest houses.  Traditionally a blended wine dominated by large producers, Champagne has in recent years seen a surge in récoltant manipulant wines - small-lot, grower-produced wines bottled by the farmers who grew the grapes.  But can bigger still mean better?\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>A comprehensive exploration and tasting of Champagnes from the finest houses.</h3>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKruth will examine the Grande Marques and their historical dominance in the marketplace.  We’ll taste through a line-up of the very best names in Champagne – brands synonymous with luxury – as we assess the quality and contemporary value of these legendary bubbles.\r\n\r\n<strong>Wines to poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nRiunart Blanc de Blancs\r\nDom Ruinart Blanc de Blancs 2006\r\n\r\nLouis Roederer Brut Premier\r\nLouis Roederer Cristal 2009\r\n\r\nBollinger Brut Special Cuvée\r\nBollinger Grande Année 2007\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(43398,2117,'_event_content','field_5a621095d626c'),(43399,2117,'event_package',''),(43400,2117,'_event_package','field_5a6222a9f43c7'),(43401,2117,'even