ize\";s:6:\"medium\";s:7:\"library\";s:3:\"all\";s:9:\"min_width\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"min_height\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"min_size\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"max_width\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"max_height\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"max_size\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"mime_types\";s:0:\"\";}','Photo','photo','publish','closed','closed','','field_5a6a6e7f17346','','','2018-02-13 06:13:49','2018-02-13 06:13:49','',203,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=acf-field&#038;p=209',6,'acf-field','',0),(210,1,'2018-01-26 00:39:07','2018-01-26 00:39:07','a:7:{s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"url\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";i:0;s:17:\"conditional_logic\";i:0;s:7:\"wrapper\";a:3:{s:5:\"width\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";}s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:0:\"\";}','Website','website','publish','closed','closed','','field_5a6a76f16e540','','','2018-02-13 06:13:49','2018-02-13 06:13:49','',203,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=acf-field&#038;p=210',2,'acf-field','',0),(215,3,'2018-01-30 21:56:46','2018-01-30 21:56:46','The pinnacle of the weekend, our walk-around style Grand Champagne tasting is an all-out homage to Champagne in all its varied expressions.\r\n\r\nWe’ve carefully curated a line-up of the region’s finest – from rare artisanal grower Champagnes made in miniscule quantities to extraordinary vintage bottlings to tête de cuvée trophy wines from the legendary Grande Marques, this is the place to taste them all in one location.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>This is the must-attend event in Los Angeles for anyone serious about Champagne</h3>\r\n&nbsp;</blockquote>\r\nNo other event in America has yet offered this kind of comprehensive tasting opportunity for both aspiring enthusiasts and seasoned collectors. It is the must-attend event in Los Angeles for anyone serious about Champagne, and we can’t wait to raise a glass (or three) with you there.','Grand Champagne Tasting','The can’t miss event of Effervescence! Join us for a grand tasting tour of Champagne and all the region has to offer. Come anytime, but we recommend joining us by 3:30pm. All wines are included in the ticket price!','publish','closed','closed','','grand-champagne-tasting','','','2018-05-06 23:42:16','2018-05-06 23:42:16','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=215',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(228,5,'2018-02-01 18:46:58','2018-02-01 18:46:58','We are deeply honored to host expert author Richard Juhlin, widely considered to be the foremost Champagne connoisseur in the world. Juhlin has published extensively on Champagne and is reputed to have tasted more of it than anyone else over the course of his long and varied career. From James Beard awards to France’s Legion d’Honneur, Juhlin is particularly revered for his blind-tasting abilities and encyclopedic knowledge of the region.\r\n\r\nFor this Master Class, Juhlin will guide us as we examine - and taste - how Champagne ages and matures through four decades - 1970, 1980, 1990 and 2000. We\'ll be treated to rarities not commonly available as we explore both youthful and aged examples of the region\'s very best bottlings.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>How do both terroir and chemistry impact an aging bottle?</h3>\r\n&nbsp;</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Some of the topics covered during this unique master class: </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">What is the golden age for Champagne at the moment?</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Have production methods changed over the decades, and how does this reflect the style today?</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Does the feeling of terroir change with maturity?</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The concept of Œnothèque &amp; Vinothèque</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 2009\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 2006\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 2000 P2\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 1996 P2\r\n\r\nDom Pérignon 1988 P3\r\n\r\nTaittinger Vintage 1976','Mature Champagnes - How Champagne Ages Over the Years','Swedish Champagne expert Richard Juhlin, in a rare US appearance, will conduct a master class on how mature Champagne evolves through the years.\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.','publish','closed','closed','','master-class-mature-champagnes','','','2018-05-06 23:42:59','2018-05-06 23:42:59','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=228',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(229,4,'2018-02-01 23:12:26','2018-02-01 23:12:26','For Effervescence\'s inaugural Collector Champagne Dinner, Krug winemaker Jérôme Jacoillot will take guests through a memorable evening of Krug Champagnes.  A bespoke menu has been created by esteemed Chef Casey Lane of Viale dei Romani, with each course paired to the Champagnes on show. The line up will include seven different Krug Vintages and two of the most iconic wines of the World, Krug Clos du Mesnil 2002, which Jérôme is responsible for, and Krug Clos d\'Ambonnay 2002.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>This is an evening that Krug lovers will not want to miss!</h3>\r\n&nbsp;</blockquote>\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nKrug Grande Cuvée en Jeroboam\r\n\r\nKrug Grande Cuvée\r\n\r\nKrug Clos du Mesnil 2002\r\n\r\nKrug Clos d’Ambonnay 2002\r\n\r\nKrug Rosé en magnum\r\n\r\nKrug 2004\r\n\r\nKrug 2002\r\n\r\nKrug 2000\r\n\r\nKrug 1998\r\n\r\nKrug 1996\r\n\r\nKrug 1995\r\n\r\nKrug Collection 1990\r\n<h5></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>Please note that tickets to this event are very limited.</h5>','Krug Lovers Dinner','Join Krug winemaker Jérôme Jacoillot and a group of Krug lovers for a night of exclusive treasures and the cuisine of Chef Casey Lane.\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.','publish','closed','closed','','collectors-champagne-dinner','','','2018-05-06 23:42:38','2018-05-06 23:42:38','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=229',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(231,5,'2018-02-01 19:04:32','2018-02-01 19:04:32','For our first annual Collector Champagne Luncheon, we are excited to celebrate the 200th anniversary of Billecart-Salmon with special guest Geoffrey Loisel, Director North America, Champagne Billecart-Salmon.\r\n\r\nAdding to the festivities, only guests at the luncheon will be able to bid on the sole known magnum of Nicolas Francois 1961. Sourced from the Domaine and presented by Geoffrey Loisel himself.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2042\" src=\"https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/B--800x441.jpg\" alt=\"B-S farm house\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: transparent; color: #333333; cursor: text; font-family: Georgia,\'Times New Roman\',\'Bitstream Charter\',Times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;\">C</span><span style=\"display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: transparent; color: #333333; cursor: text; font-family: Georgia,\'Times New Roman\',\'Bitstream Charter\',Times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;\">hef Walter Manzke will treat a select group of Champagne aficionados at his République restaurant to an extraordinary meal, paired with truly extraordinary wines. Expect multiple courses prepared to par with an outstanding lineup of Billecart-Salmon Champagnes, listed below.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nReception wine: NV Extra Brut en magnum\r\nNV Brut Reserve\r\nNV Brut Rosé en magnum\r\nNV Brut Sous Bois\r\nNV Cuvée 200 en magnum\r\n2007 Vintage Extra Brut\r\n2006 Blanc de Blancs Grand Cru\r\n2004 Blanc de Blancs Grand Cru en magnum\r\n2006 Nicolas Francois Billecart Grand Cru\r\n2002 Nicolas Francois Billecart Grand Cru en magnum\r\n1996 Nicolas Francois Billecart Grand Cru\r\n1998 Cuvée Elizabeth Salmon Grand Cru\r\n1996 Cuvée Elizabeth Salmon Grand Cru\r\n1999 Le Clos Saint-Hilaire\r\n1996 Le Clos Saint-Hilaire\r\n<h5><span style=\"display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: transparent; color: #333333; cursor: text; font-family: Georgia,\'Times New Roman\',\'Bitstream Charter\',Times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;\">Note that seats at this luncheon are very limited.</span></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Billecart-Salmon Collector Luncheon','Enjoy a sumptuous tasting menu by Chef Walter Manzke celebrating Billecart-Salmon’s 200th Anniversary. Only those in attendance will have the opportunity to bid on the sole known Magnum of Nicolas Francois 1961. \r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.','publish','closed','closed','','collectors-champagne-lunch-republique','','','2018-05-06 23:39:39','2018-05-06 23:39:39','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=231',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(232,5,'2018-02-13 21:34:02','2018-02-13 21:34:02','On Friday afternoon and evening, we lighten and loosen up a bit in a no-holds-barred Bacchanalia of everything bubbly. The historic Avalon Hollywood nightclub will be transformed into a drinker’s delight, with sparkling wines from every corner of the globe.\r\n\r\nThis walk-around tasting is designed to be fun and informative, for both novices and experts alike. Come sample prosecco, moscato, Lambrusco, cava, sekt, crémants and delicious American bubbles sourced from the finest international producers.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>Join us to sample prosecco, moscato, Lambrusco, cava and others.</h3>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe evening will end with the first <a href=\"http://effervescencela.com/sommeliers/#competition\">Best Sparkling Somm</a> finals, where you will get to see today\'s best sommeliers compete against each other.\r\n\r\nCome curious - this tasting will offer some fun and unusual wines. Cheers!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','More Bubbles Sparkling Wine Extravaganza','A walk-around style tasting featuring sparkling wines from Spain, USA, France, England, Italy, Austria and beyond. Come anytime, but we recommend joining us by 7:30pm. All wines are included in the ticket price!','publish','closed','closed','','bubbles-sparkling-wine-extravanga','','','2018-05-15 06:35:44','2018-05-15 06:35:44','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=232',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(236,5,'2018-02-01 22:14:06','2018-02-01 22:14:06','\"Champagne is the only wine that can accommodate all of nature\'s fragrances in a single glass. Its unsurpassed aromatic diversity makes it possible to pick up all types of nature and fragrances and create harmony with the environment. By virtue of the character and fragrance of the location, different aspects of the Champagne\'s personality will be highlighted and reinforced. This is the heart of the matter, and the reason why I do not devote myself to Wine Hiking but instead created the concept of <em>Champagne Hiking</em>\"\r\n\r\n<em>Richard Juhlin</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRichard Juhlin’s most recent book, <em><a href=\"https://champagnehiking.tictail.com\">Champagne Hiking</a>,</em> offers a compelling examination of how Champagne is experienced differently by consuming it in different locations. Does the environment in which we open a bottle impact our sensory perception of it? Does bubbly taste better at higher altitudes? Juhlin will explore the science behind the phenomenon as the nature of Champagne interacts with Mother Nature – expect the unexpected at this tasting!\r\n\r\nSome of the topics covered during this unique master class:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The environmental impact on the drinking experience</li>\r\n 	<li>Why Champagne tastes the best at a particular time, in a particular place</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nAubry \'Le Nombre d\'Or\' Brut NV\r\nAndré Clouet Millesime 2008\r\nDe Sousa Blanc de Blancs Reserve Grand Cru NV\r\nMarc Hebrart \'Selection\' Brut NV\r\nLouis Roederer Brut Rose 2010\r\nBollinger\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1863\" src=\"https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Book-Notebook-in-Wooden-Case-2-800x655.png\" alt=\"Champagne Hiking Book\" width=\"800\" height=\"655\" />\r\n\r\nTo place an order on <i>Champagne Hiking</i> online, please visit the Champagne Hiking Store <a href=\"https://champagnehiking.tictail.com\">here</a>.','Champagne Hiking - The Missing Piece','Experience the beauty of our world through a glass of champagne with Richard Juhlin, author of <i>The Scent of Champagne</i>. A master class on how our environment influences our perception of Champagne!\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.','publish','closed','closed','','masterclass-champagne-hiking-richard-juhlin','','','2018-05-06 23:40:30','2018-05-06 23:40:30','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=236',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(239,4,'2018-02-01 23:16:10','2018-02-01 23:16:10','','RJ3','','inherit','open','closed','','rj3','','','2018-02-01 23:56:02','2018-02-01 23:56:02','',244,'https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/RJ3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(240,4,'2018-02-01 23:18:02','2018-02-01 23:18:02','','RJ4','','inherit','open','closed','','rj4','','','2018-02-01 23:53:15','2018-02-01 23:53:15','',244,'https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/RJ4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(241,4,'2018-02-01 23:18:15','2018-02-01 23:18:15','','RJ1','','inherit','open','closed','','rj1','','','2018-02-01 23:52:19','2018-02-01 23:52:19','',244,'https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/RJ1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(243,4,'2018-02-09 20:53:13','2018-02-09 20:53:13','Join Master Sommelier and noted wine educator Geoff Kruth for this comprehensive exploration and tasting of Champagnes from the finest houses.  Traditionally a blended wine dominated by large producers, Champagne has in recent years seen a surge in récoltant manipulant wines - small-lot, grower-produced wines bottled by the farmers who grew the grapes.  But can bigger still mean better?\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>A comprehensive exploration and tasting of Champagnes from the finest houses.</h3>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKruth will examine the Grande Marques and their historical dominance in the marketplace.  We’ll taste through a line-up of the very best names in Champagne – brands synonymous with luxury – as we assess the quality and contemporary value of these legendary bubbles.\r\n\r\n<strong>Wines to poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nRiunart Blanc de Blancs\r\nDom Ruinart Blanc de Blancs 2006\r\n\r\nLouis Roederer Brut Premier\r\nLouis Roederer Cristal 2009\r\n\r\nBollinger Brut Special Cuvée\r\nBollinger Grande Année 2007\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Style and Substance – The Triumph of the Grande Marques','Master Sommelier Geoff Kruth on the role of big Champagne houses in the modern market.\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to purchase tickets by phone, please call one of the numbers below, leave your name and number and we will gladly reach out to take your order: <a href=\"tel://323.499.8678\">323.499.8678</a> and <a href=\"tel://323.937.9463\">323.937.9463</a>.','publish','closed','closed','','grand-marques-reconsidered','','','2018-05-06 23:43:53','2018-05-06 23:43:53','',0,'https://effervescencela.com/?post_type=efrvs_event&#038;p=243',0,'efrvs_event','',0),(244,4,'2018-02-12 21:48:54','2018-02-12 21:48:54','While Champagne holds its place as the world leader in sparkling wine production, the rest of the planet has been busily catching up.  Increasingly, American market share is divided amidst high-quality sparkling wines from Italy, Spain, Germany, Austria and the US. (Just don’t call them Champagne!)\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h3>An examination of international sparkling wines sourced from around the globe.</h3>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPatrick Comiskey, lead wine writer for the <em>Los Angeles Times</em> among many other publications, joins Effervescence to lead an examination of international sparkling wines sourced from around the globe.  From Italian winners like prosecco, moscato and Franciacorta bubblies to sensational Spanish cava and top-notch American sparklers, there’s a growing world of sparkling wines to be discovered and at all price-points too.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Wines to be poured:</strong>\r\n\r\nRidgeview 2014 Cavendish Brut\r\nHush Heath Balfour BdB\r\n\r\nDom de Montbourgeau Cremant de Jura\r\nFrancois Chidaine Montlouis Brut Nature\r\n\r\nAnalemma 2013 Atavus BdN\r\nIron Horse 201