,42,'term_photo','451'),(220,42,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(221,42,'participants_clone_term_meta',''),(222,42,'_participants_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fd4fc5562'),(223,43,'term_lname','Comiskey'),(224,43,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(225,43,'term_organization_name','Patrick Comiskey, Author'),(226,43,'_term_organization_name','field_5a696b2b7a980'),(227,43,'term_outbound_url','http://www.patrickcomiskey.com'),(228,43,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(229,43,'term_photo','466'),(230,43,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(231,43,'participants_clone_term_meta',''),(232,43,'_participants_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fd4fc5562'),(233,44,'term_lname','Veuve'),(234,44,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(235,44,'term_description','The iconic yellow label of Veuve Clicquot needs no introduction – synonymous with both high quality Champagne and its history, the story of the intrepid widow Clicquot is the story of the region itself.  From entry-level blends to vintage wines to prestige cuvées, the Clicquot portfolio offers quality at every price point.'),(236,44,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(237,44,'term_outbound_url','https://www.veuveclicquot.com/fr-fr'),(238,44,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(239,44,'term_logo','621'),(240,44,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(241,44,'term_photo',''),(242,44,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(243,44,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(244,44,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(269,38,'term_logo','593'),(270,38,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(271,38,'term_description','Growing up as a child in San Diego, Walter Manzke learned the ways of seasonal cuisine at a young age. The family table was filled with organic, farm-fresh vegetables surrounding his home. This approach to eating has stuck with Manzke throughout his culinary career.  In 1992, Manzke graduated from San Diego Mesa college with a degree in Business and Restaurant Management. Upon graduation, Manzke worked in many renowned kitchens in both Los Angeles and Europe, where he developed his signature style. He has earned a number of accolades, including a three-star review from the Los Angeles Times while at Patina restaurant.\r\n\r\nIn 2002, Manzke opened three successful restaurants in Carmel: Bouchee, Cantinetta Luca and L’Auberge Carmel. At L’Auberge Carmel, Manzke was named,” Bon Appétit magazine’s “Best of the Year” and one of Gourmet magazine’s “Top Fifty Restaurants in America.”  Manzke returned to Los Angeles in 2007 to take the helm at Bastide Restaurant where he earned a three-star review from the Los Angeles Times. In 2009, Manzke joined the team at Church and State.\r\n\r\nIn the summer of 2012, Manzke, together with his wife Margarita and his sister-in-law, opened Wildflour bakery and café in Manila, Philippines and have expanded to four more locations. In Los Angeles, Manzke has opened Petty Cash Taqueria and Republique. Most recently the Manzke’s opened a Filipino food kiosk, Sari Sari Store at Grand Central Market in Downtown Los Angeles.'),(272,38,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(281,37,'term_logo','594'),(282,37,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(283,37,'term_description','Casey Lane is chef and owner of The Tasting Kitchen in Venice, California, Casa Apicii in New York\'s Greenwich Village and Viale dei Romani in West Hollywood.\r\n\r\nAfter a childhood spent drawn to his Marseilles-born mother and grandfather’s cooking for family gatherings, Lane decided to attend culinary school in Portland based on his simple belief that “the best food in the world only ever comes from farmland.” After graduating and getting his professional start in banquet catering, Lane began cooking at Portland’s Clarklewis restaurant in 2003. At Clarklewis, Lane would spend the next five years under Chef Morgan Brownlow developing his skills and knowledge about true farm-to-table cooking. His experience with Chef Brownlow would serve as the guiding principles of his own culinary style in the years to come.\r\n\r\nIn 2009, Lane moved to Los Angeles and was given the opportunity to reboot a Scandinavian restaurant on Abbot Kinney Boulevard in Venice called AK. With little more than a handwritten menu and minor subsequent renovations, Lane\'s cooking alone transformed the space into The Tasting Kitchen, which remains one of LA’s most popular neighborhood staples. Lane was awarded multiple “best of” accolades from GQ, Food &amp; Wine, Los Angeles Magazine and more that year, which initiated a four-year-long run as a semi-finalist for the James Beard Foundation’s ‘Rising Star Chef of the Year’ award. “The Tasting Kitchen has prepared some of the most delicious food I’ve eaten all year,” wrote Jonathan Gold in a 2009 LA Weekly review.\r\n\r\nWe are thrilled to announce that our exclusive Krug Lovers Dinner will be prepared by Chef Casey Lane at his white-hot new restaurant in the Hotel La Peer in West Hollywood. Lane’s career trajectory culminates at Viale dei Romani, where his deft touch with both European technique and California’s local bounty are given full expression.'),(284,37,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(289,42,'term_logo','457'),(290,42,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(291,42,'term_description','Master Sommelier Geoff Kruth launched the GuildSomm website in 2009, joining his career in wine with his early background in technology. He manages the organization, hosts the GuildSomm audio podcast and video documentaries, develops content, and leads masterclasses. Geoff also travels and speaks extensively, promoting GuildSomm, wine education, and the sommelier profession.\r\n\r\nHe co-produced the documentary film “Into the Bottle”, the follow-up to the cult documentary hit SOMM as well as producing and starring in the TV show Uncorked on NBC’s Esquire network. Mr Kruth is also the proprietor of Lost &amp; Found Winery in Sonoma County.'),(292,42,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(293,43,'term_logo','465'),(294,43,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(295,43,'term_description','Patrick Comiskey is a Senior Correspondent for Wine &amp; Spirits Magazine, where he serves as chief critic for all American wines not from California, and regularly contributes feature articles on California, Oregon and Washington wine, winegrowing, and wine culture. He is a regular contributor of articles on wine and restaurant culture for the Los Angeles Times, where he’s the chief wine writer for the newspaper. His work has appeared in the San Francisco Chronicle, Food and Wine, Bon Appetit, Decanter, Lucky Peach, Zester Daily, and the Robb Report. His book American Rhône: How Maverick Winemakers Changed the Way Americans Drink was published in October, 2016. In 2017, the book was shortlisted for both the Andre Simon Book Awards and the Louis Roederer Wine Book Awards; it won the Gourmand Prize for Best New World Wine Book.'),(296,43,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(297,41,'term_logo','456'),(298,41,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(299,41,'term_description','Richard Juhlin is widely considered to be the world’s number one Champagne expert.  He’s legendary for his skills in blind tasting, including the 2003 “Spectacle du Monde” tasting in Paris in which Juhlin correctly identified 43 out of 50 Champagnes.\r\n\r\nHe’s widely published as an author, including titles like “Champagneboken” (1995), “2000 Champagnes” (1999), “The Great Tasting” (2000), “3000 Champagnes” (2002), “4000 Champagnes” (2004), “Richard Juhlin Champagne Guide” (2008), \"A Scent Of Champagne” (2013) and his most recent title ”<a href=\"https://champagnehiking.tictail.com\">Champagne Hiking</a>” (2017).\r\n\r\nHis long list of honors and awards received in recognition of his tireless promotion of the region are perhaps best epitomized in the words of former French President François Hollande when he graced Juhlin with France’s top tribute, the Chevalier of the Legion of Honor in 2013:  “By listing more than 10,000 tasting notes of Champagne, Mr. Richard Juhlin has established himself as one of the best connoisseurs of Champagne in the world and one of the most influential promoters of this French know-how (savoir-faire). His outstanding work, carried out with determination for more than 20 years, has contributed significantly to the spread of Champagne in Sweden &amp; the world, but also to the promotion of the Champagne-Ardenne region here. In appointing Richard Juhlin Chevalier of the Legion of Honor, the French authorities wanted to pay tribute to his work of passion and promotion of Champagne.”\r\n\r\nWe are very honored to host Richard Juhlin as our esteemed guest at our inaugural Effervescence event.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),(300,41,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(313,8,'venue_address',''),(314,8,'_venue_address','field_5a626ef64504f'),(315,8,'venue_phone',''),(316,8,'_venue_phone','field_5a626f4c45051'),(317,8,'venue_note',''),(318,8,'_venue_note','field_5a626f5c45052'),(319,40,'venue_image_a','473'),(320,40,'_venue_image_a','field_5a83bdd4f0958'),(321,40,'venue_image_b','469'),(322,40,'_venue_image_b','field_5a83bde9f0959'),(323,39,'venue_image_a','1323'),(324,39,'_venue_image_a','field_5a83bdd4f0958'),(325,39,'venue_image_b','569'),(326,39,'_venue_image_b','field_5a83bde9f0959'),(327,36,'venue_image_a','478'),(328,36,'_venue_image_a','field_5a83bdd4f0958'),(329,36,'venue_image_b','477'),(330,36,'_venue_image_b','field_5a83bde9f0959'),(331,8,'venue_image_a',''),(332,8,'_venue_image_a','field_5a83bdd4f0958'),(333,8,'venue_image_b',''),(334,8,'_venue_image_b','field_5a83bde9f0959'),(335,15,'term_lname','Agrapart'),(336,15,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(337,15,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagne-agrapart.com/en/'),(338,15,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(339,16,'term_lname','André'),(340,16,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(341,16,'term_description','Jean-François Clouet, who was born and raised in Bouzy, still lives in the 18th century village house built by his ancestors. As his family was the official printer to Louis XV’s Royal Court at Versailles, Jean-François takes great pride in his lineage.\r\n\r\nAcknowledging the good fortune of his background, Jean-François strives to continually improve upon the estate and its wines by implementing changes that ultimately improve the quality of his wines.  The domaine’s 20 acres of Grand Cru vineyards are situated in the coveted middle slopes of Ambonnay and Bouzy. They make a full range of Champagnes, including most famously the glorious Cuvée 1911, which is comprised of 100% Pinot Noir from Clouet’s ten best lieux-dits in Bouzy.'),(342,16,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(343,16,'term_outbound_url','http://www.sacredthirstselections.com/andr-clouet/'),(344,16,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(345,16,'term_logo','624'),(346,16,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(347,16,'term_photo',''),(348,16,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(349,16,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(350,16,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(351,47,'term_lname','Billecart'),(352,47,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(353,47,'term_description','Champagne Billecart-Salmon is located in the charming village of Mareuil-sur-Aÿ, Founded in 1818 with the auspicious marriage of Nicolas François Billecart and Elisabeth Salmon, we are honored to celebrate the 200 year anniversary of this remarkable family-owned house whose motto is \"to privilege quality, to strive for excellence.”'),(354,47,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(355,47,'term_outbound_url','https://www.champagne-billecart.fr/index.php'),(356,47,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(357,47,'term_logo','567'),(358,47,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(359,47,'term_photo',''),(360,47,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(361,47,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(362,47,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(363,48,'term_lname','Bollinger'),(364,48,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(365,48,'term_description','Champagne Bollinger has created prestigious wines with character, distinguished by their elegance and complexity, since 1829. These outstanding Champagnes are the result of rigorous attention to detail, for Bollinger accepts nothing less than excellence. Each and every detail represents a quest for a certain form of perfection.\r\n\r\nThis uncompromisingly independent spirit, dedicated to unostentatious achievement, exemplifies the inimitable elegance for which the Champagne region is renowned.'),(366,48,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(367,48,'term_outbound_url','https://www.champagne-bollinger.com/'),(368,48,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(369,48,'term_logo','566'),(370,48,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(371,48,'term_photo',''),(372,48,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(373,48,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(374,48,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(375,49,'term_lname','de Sousa'),(376,49,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(377,49,'term_description','Located in the heart of the prestigious “Côte des Blancs,” Domaine de Sousa has been in existence for three generations, on renowned soils listed as Grands Crus (Avize, Cramant, and Oger). De Sousa Winery has been devoted to authenticity and quality since its inception. Their cultivation of older vines, use of organic fertilizer, and respect for the terroir have produced exceptional quality wines of extraordinary value since 1986.'),(378,49,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(379,49,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagnedesousa.com/en/'),(380,49,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(381,49,'term_logo','601'),(382,49,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(383,49,'term_photo',''),(384,49,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(385,49,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(386,49,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(399,51,'term_lname','Dom'),(400,51,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(401,51,'term_description','Lovers of legendary Champagne need no introduction to Dom Pérignon, the prestige cuvée of powerhouse Moët &amp; Chandon.  Made only in extraordinary years, Dom Pérignon is always a vintage-designate tête de cuvée wine that is designed for extraordinary ageing.'),(402,51,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(403,51,'term_outbound_url','https://www.domperignon.com/us-en/'),(404,51,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(405,51,'term_logo','441'),(406,51,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(407,51,'term_photo',''),(408,51,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(409,51,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(410,51,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(411,52,'term_lname','eric'),(412,52,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(413,52,'term_description','The Rodez family has been making wine for nine generations, beginning as far back as 1757.  The estate of Champagne Rodez is located in the Grand Cru that is Ambonnay, the heart of Pinot Noir country, and spans an area of 6.12 hectares.  The property consists of 35 parcels of vines, and the grape varietals planted are 62% Pinot Noir and 38% Chardonnay.  The vineyards are planted at a fairly-high altitude (about 130 meters), and are situated on a clay-limestone soil, two factors which are ideal for growing Pinot Noir.\r\n\r\nEric Rodez, current vineyard manager and head oenologist for the estate, has worn many hats in his day.  Not only was he at one time the Mayor of Ambonnay, but he was also formerly an oenologist at Krug where he developed his winemaking/blending methods that would later be employed on his own estate.  Eric, along with his wife Martine and son Mickael, manages all aspects of the winemaking process at Champagne Rodez.'),(414,52,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(415,52,'term_outbound_url','http://www.apwineimports.com/us/services/champagne-rodez/'),(416,52,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(417,52,'term_logo','572'),(418,52,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(419,52,'term_photo',''),(420,52,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(421,52,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(422,52,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(423,53,'term_lname','Guiborat'),(424,53,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(425,53,'term_description','The Fouquet family has farmed small parcels in Cramant, Champagne since 1885. At the helm now is 5th generation Richard Fouquet and his wife Karine (though if you were to visit you may find his grandmother keeping a watchful eye – in her mid 90’s and still sharp as a tack!).\r\n\r\nThe Fouquets farm eight hectares, most of which are Grand Cru holdings from the deep chalk of Cramant and Chouilly, as well as vineyards in Mardeuil on the other side of Épernay.  The domaine’s overall production is tiny, as grapes from five of these eight hectares are regularly sold to the Champagne house of Laurent-Perrier. Viticulture is focused on producing top quality Chardonnay from the two former villages with the rest of their holdings being Pinot Meunier from the latter. Farming is all done by hand, with aggressive pruning and low yields.'),(426,53,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(427,53,'term_outbound_url','http://www.sacredthirstselections.com/guiborat-fils'),(428,53,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(429,53,'term_logo','606'),(430,53,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(431,53,'term_photo',''),(432,53,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(433,53,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(434,53,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(435,54,'term_lname','Huré'),(436,54,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(437,54,'term_description','A close-knit family, two brothers sharing a common vision and then passing on their values to the next generation…all this and more make up the story of Champagne Huré-Fréres, started just over 50 years ago and still very much a family business. Today Raoul Huré and his two sons, Francois and Pierre invite you to discover their maison at Ludes in the Montagne de Reims.'),(438,54,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(439,54,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagne-hure-freres.com/'),(440,54,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(441,54,'term_logo','574'),(442,54,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(443,54,'term_photo',''),(444,54,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(445,54,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(446,54,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(447,55,'term_lname','Jacquesson'),(448,55,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(449,55,'term_description','Jacquesson is one of Champagne’s most venerable houses, not only predating Krug, but giving birth to it, when in 1843 Johann-Joseph Krug left Jacquesson to form his own house.\r\n\r\nBut despite more than 200 years of history, Jacquesson has become a revolutionary among Champagne’s established houses, under the leadership of brothers Laurent and Jean-Hervé Chiquet, who took over from their father in the 1980’s. Since then, the house has adopted a herbicide-free, terroir-based philosophy. It also retired, after 150 years, its non-vintage blend and replaced it with a groundbreaking single-vintage-based cuvée, which changes yearly. And next came its terroir-based cuvées, an unprecedented move for a traditional house.  As Champagne lovers have the chance to experience more and more of Jacquesson’s new releases, the genius of this house’s ideas is coming more fully into focus.'),(450,55,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(451,55,'term_outbound_url','https://www.champagnejacquesson.com/en'),(452,55,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(453,55,'term_logo','608'),(454,55,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(455,55,'term_photo',''),(456,55,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(457,55,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(458,55,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(459,56,'term_lname','Krug'),(460,56,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(461,56,'term_description','Behind every precious drop of Krug stands the dream of a visionary. One man who, long before others, understood that the essence of Champagne is pleasure.\r\n\r\nSo, over 170 years ago, Joseph Krug broke with convention to follow his vision. To create the most generous expression of Champagne every year, regardless of climatic unpredictability.\r\n\r\nJoseph’s bold experiment proved a triumph and he succeeded in creating a Champagne that is truly without compare. To this day, the House of Krug lives and breathes his enduring philosophy, creating only prestige Champagnes since 1843.'),(462,56,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(463,56,'term_outbound_url','https://www.krug.com/'),(464,56,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(465,56,'term_logo','1548'),(466,56,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(467,56,'term_photo',''),(468,56,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(469,56,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(470,56,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(471,57,'term_lname','Lanson'),(472,57,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(473,57,'term_description','The House of Lanson was founded in 1760 by François Delamotte, an influential character in Reims society. The joint owner, alongside his wife, of a not-insubstantial vineyard in Cumières and Ay, he decided to found his own Champagne house – one of the very first ever to exist. In 1798, Nicolas-Louis Delamotte, his younger son, took over from his father. Having been admitted as a knight of the Order of Malta at a very young age, he decided to use the Maltese Cross as the House’s emblem. Now revised, the Lanson cross has become the icon of the company.'),(474,57,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(475,57,'term_outbound_url','http://www.lanson.com/en/'),(476,57,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(477,57,'term_logo','610'),(478,57,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(479,57,'term_photo',''),(480,57,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(481,57,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(482,57,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(495,59,'term_lname','Marion'),(496,59,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(497,59,'term_description','It is in Hautvillers, a world UNESCO heritage site and the famous village where monk Dom Pérignon made his auspicious discovery, that we find the rising house of Marion-Bosser.  This is a family that has cultivated the vineyard with care, rigor and passion for the soil, for more than a century. This legendary name was revived in 1994 by Bernadette Marion-Bosser and today daughter Elodie, an accomplished young viticulturist and savvy marketer, has taken over the winemaking duties.  This is an extraordinary Champagne to watch as it is rediscovered on the international scene.'),(498,59,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(499,59,'term_outbound_url','http://champagnemarionbosser.fr/'),(500,59,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(501,59,'term_logo','611'),(502,59,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(503,59,'term_photo',''),(504,59,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(505,59,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(506,59,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(507,60,'term_lname','Moët'),(508,60,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(509,60,'term_description','Synonymous with luxury, the wines of Moët &amp; Chandon epitomize the region of Champagne.  From entry-level bubblies made with passion and precision to rarities that grace the cellars of collectors around the world, Moët &amp; Chandon is one of the icons of the industry.'),(510,60,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(511,60,'term_outbound_url','https://us.moet.com/'),(512,60,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(513,60,'term_logo','570'),(514,60,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(515,60,'term_photo',''),(516,60,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(517,60,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(518,60,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(519,61,'term_lname','Moussé'),(520,61,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(521,61,'term_description','A grower since 1750, Champagne Moussé sits in the village of Cuisles, in a valley perpendicular to the Vallée de la Marne. This side valley has a unique soil in Champagne: a schist subsoil under clay. While pinot meunier often struggles to be taken seriously in Champagne, at Moussé, pinot meunier is celebrated. 80% of the vines planted are meunier, with the balance planted to pinot noir and chardonnay.'),(522,61,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(523,61,'term_outbound_url','http://champagnemoussefils.com/'),(524,61,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(525,61,'term_logo','614'),(526,61,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(527,61,'term_photo',''),(528,61,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(529,61,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(530,61,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(531,62,'term_lname','Philipponnat '),(532,62,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(533,62,'term_description','The corporate changes that have swept through Champagne in recent years seem sure to rob many old houses of their connection to the past. But one small jewel of a house is moving ever closer to its roots: Philipponnat.  It is one of the last houses to be run by a member of its founding family. And Charles Philipponnat is a true Champenois, descended from winemakers, cellarmasters and growers dating back nearly 600 years.Champagne is in Charles’ blood, and this helps to explain Philipponnat’s recent resurgence. Twenty years ago, the house was known largely for its iconic Clos des Goisses—the majestic tête de cuvée made from Champagne’s single greatest vineyard.  But under Charles, Philipponnat is gaining reverence for its entire portfolio of richly expressive Champagnes.  Through great vision, technical skill and perfectionist attention to detail–and the pride of five centuries of tradition–Charles has created a range of Champagnes with few peers for quality and character. This ranges from the towering Clos des Goisses to the superb Royale Réserve and Reserve Rosé, two of the finest non-vintage brut Champagnes on the market today.'),(534,62,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(535,62,'term_outbound_url','http://www.philipponnat.com/'),(536,62,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(537,62,'term_logo','616'),(538,62,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(539,62,'term_photo',''),(540,62,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(541,62,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(542,62,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(543,63,'term_lname','Pierre'),(544,63,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(545,63,'term_description','The Pierre Péters estate, situated in the heart of the \"Côte des Blancs\" in the village of Le Mesnil sur Oger, has been a family house for six generations and has produced Grand Cru Blanc de Blancs Champagnes since 1919. As a Champagne grower-producer, their wines come exclusively from their own vineyards. The house currently operates on just over 19 hectares of Chardonnay, mainly located in the communes of Le Mesnil sur Oger, Oger, Avize and Cramant. The family has developed - from generation to generation - its own selection of grapes. They have been able to maintain and age their vineyards which are now 30-years old on average. Each year out of respect for the environment, they adapt their cultivation methods to obtain healthy grapes so that their Champagne expresses more precisely the richness, subtlety and the elegance of the great \"terroirs\" of the Côte des Blancs.'),(546,63,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(547,63,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagne-peters.com/en/home'),(548,63,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(549,63,'term_logo','618'),(550,63,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(551,63,'term_photo',''),(552,63,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(553,63,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(554,63,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(555,64,'term_lname','R'),(556,64,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(557,64,'term_description','Champagne R. H. Coutier is located in the grand cru village of Ambonnay, one of the top wine-producing towns on the Montagne de Reims. The Coutier family has been in the village of Ambonnay since 1619, with the current head of the family estate René Coutier. The Coutiers own nine hectares of vineyards in Ambonnay, and interestingly, although Ambonnay is generally regarded as pinot noir country, the Coutiers’ vineyards are planted with one-third chardonnay and two-thirds pinot noir. In fact, in 1946 René Coutier’s father was the first vigneron in Ambonnay to plant chardonnay in the village, which has done well over the ensuing decades and now is as highly regarded as the pinot noir from this grand cru village. The vineyards on the Montagne de Reims shift exposure as one arrives in the village of Ambonnay, facing due south and producing a rather warmer microclimate for the grapes. There is also a bit more clay and a bit less limestone in the soils of Ambonnay than is typical throughout the region, which tends to produce more sumptuous styles in the wines, such as Coutier’s, that rely solely on Ambonnay fruit. This is not a large domaine by any stretch of the imagination, only producing 25,000 bottles in any given year.'),(558,64,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(559,64,'term_outbound_url','https://polanerselections.com/producer/coutier'),(560,64,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(561,64,'term_logo',''),(562,64,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(563,64,'term_photo',''),(564,64,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(565,64,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(566,64,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(579,66,'term_lname','Ruinart'),(580,66,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(581,66,'term_description','Ruinart is the oldest established Champagne house and has been exclusively producing Champagne since 1729. Founded by Nicolas Ruinart in the Champagne region in the city of Reims, the house is today proudly represented within LVMH’s luxury portfolio, as its own legendary monk – Dom Ruinart and his extraordinary history – are revived to take their place on the world wine stage.'),(582,66,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(583,66,'term_outbound_url','https://www.ruinart.com/fr-e'),(584,66,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(585,66,'term_logo','445'),(586,66,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(587,66,'term_photo',''),(588,66,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(589,66,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(590,66,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(591,67,'term_lname','Vilmart'),(592,67,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(593,67,'term_description','Vilmart &amp; Cie. traces its history back to 1890, when it was founded by Désiré Vilmart, and from the beginning, Vilmart &amp; Cie. has always been a “récoltant-manipulant,” making Champagne exclusively from estate-owned vines. Since 1989 the estate has been in the hands of Laurent Champs, the fifth generation of the family to take the helm of the house. The majority of Vilmart’s eleven hectares of vines lies in Rilly-la-Montagne, although there are a few plots just over the border in the neighboring village of Villers-Allerand. Vilmart is a member of Ampelos, an organization that promotes organic and sustainable viticulture, and Champs has never used any herbicides or chemical fertilizers since taking over the estate. Beloved by sommeliers and made in tiny coveted quantities, the wines of Vilmart &amp; Cie are simply extraordinary.'),(594,67,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(595,67,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagnevilmart.fr/en/nos-cuvees.php'),(596,67,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(597,67,'term_logo','622'),(598,67,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(599,67,'term_photo',''),(600,67,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(601,67,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(602,67,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(603,68,'term_lname','Gusbourne'),(604,68,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(605,68,'term_description','The original Gusbourne Estate in the United Kingdom dates back to 1410. In 2004, Andrew Weeber took over the estate with a clear vision and a single goal: to create English sparkling wines that would stand up alongside the very finest offerings from across the globe. The first vines were planted that year. In 2010, the début vintages of Gusbourne Brut Reserve 2006 and Gusbourne Blanc de Blancs 2006 were released to critical acclaim. Gusbourne quickly earned a reputation as a producer of outstanding quality wines, with accolades from some of the industry\'s most exacting critics.'),(606,68,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(607,68,'term_outbound_url','https://www.gusbourne.com/'),(608,68,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(609,68,'term_logo','564'),(610,68,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(611,68,'term_photo',''),(612,68,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(613,68,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(614,68,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(615,69,'term_lname','Pere'),(616,69,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(617,69,'term_description','The Cava made by winemaker Pere Mata under the Mata Coloma winery banner has redefined the entire Spanish sparkling wine industry, proving that quality can exist alongside quantity. Pere farms just five hectares in the town of Sant Sadurní d’Anoia in the heart of the Penedès, Catalunya. The work is all organic and by hand. Pere only uses the classic grape varieties of Xarello, Macabeu and Parellada, as he feels that these are the grapes most suited to the task of speaking the terroir of Cava. The wines all spend at least 2 years on lees and some over 4 years. All of the wines are vintage dated and all have disgorgement dates listed on the back labels.  The quality and transparency of these sparkling wines inevitably brings up Champagne– but Pere is not attempting to make Champagne. He is making Cava with a level of dedication and craftsmanship that is usually associated with the world\'s greatest sparkling wine. The results are inspiring.'),(618,69,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(619,69,'term_outbound_url','http://www.coeurwineco.com/producer/mata-i-coloma/'),(620,69,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(621,69,'term_logo',''),(622,69,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(623,69,'term_photo',''),(624,69,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(625,69,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(626,69,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(627,70,'term_lname','Bichot'),(628,70,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(629,70,'term_description','Truly one of the most ancient names in Burgundy, the first traces of the Bichot family date back to 1214. They settled in their fief of Châteauneuf-en-Auxois in 1350 and established the iconic family coat of arms that has not changed in nearly 700 years.  Now helmed by Albéric Bichot, the company owns six domaines that span Burgundy and which include a growing stable of extraordinary sparkling Crémants de Bourgogne in addition to their still wines.'),(630,70,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(631,70,'term_outbound_url','https://www.albert-bichot.com/en'),(632,70,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(633,70,'term_logo','603'),(634,70,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(635,70,'term_photo',''),(636,70,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(637,70,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(638,70,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(639,71,'term_lname','M'),(640,71,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(641,71,'term_description','Two wines in the Crémant de Loire range of the Alliance Loire, the M. Bonnamy Brut and Brut Rosé are great examples of inexpensive yet delicious French sparkling wines. The grapes are predominantly grown on various forms of limestone which include most significantly Tufa (meteogene tavertine), the material widely used in the building of many châteaux throughout the Loire Valley. The Crémant de Loire Brut Rosé is comprised of 100% Cabernet Franc, while the Crémant de Loire Brut is a blend of Cabernet Franc, Chardonnay and Chenin Blanc. All of the fruit for M. Bonnamy is hand harvested, gently pressed and fermented at cool temperatures in order to retain the delicate esters and aromatics of the grapes. After an assemblage of the best lots, the wines undergo a second fermentation and ageing in the bottle for 12 months before being disgorged.'),(642,71,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(643,71,'term_outbound_url','https://chwine.com/m-bonnamy-cremant-de-loire-brut'),(644,71,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(645,71,'term_logo',''),(646,71,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(647,71,'term_photo',''),(648,71,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(649,71,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(650,71,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(651,72,'term_lname','Eric'),(652,72,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(653,72,'term_description','In 1992, Eric Bordelet who was previously the sommelier at Arpège, Alain Passard\'s Restaurant in Paris, took over the production of this family property in Normandy. Believing that apple and pear bubblies should be produced with the same attention received by fine wine grapes, Bordolet now grows more than twenty varieties of apple and fifteen varieties of pear.  Connoisseurs admire his entirely artisanal approach and commitment to biodynamic farming, and his sparkling sydres are extraordinary.'),(654,72,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(655,72,'term_outbound_url','http://www.ericbordelet.com/english.html'),(656,72,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(657,72,'term_logo','604'),(658,72,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(659,72,'term_photo',''),(660,72,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(661,72,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(662,72,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(663,73,'term_lname','François'),(664,73,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(665,73,'term_description','In 1989, François Chidaine moved to Montlouis-