 Sussex’s successful Ridgeview Wine Estates has proved doubters wrong.  Founded by Mike and Chris Roberts, who sensed an opportunity within the chalky soils of South Downs, Ridgeview’s sparkling wine production focuses on the trio of classic Champagne varieties – chardonnay, pinot noir and pinot meunier.   Among other awards, Decanter magazine named it the best sparkling wine in the world in 2010.'),(1254,112,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1255,112,'term_outbound_url','https://www.ridgeview.co.uk/'),(1256,112,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1257,112,'term_logo','767'),(1258,112,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1259,112,'term_photo',''),(1260,112,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1261,112,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1262,112,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1263,113,'term_banner_image',''),(1264,113,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1265,113,'term_lname','Riverbench'),(1266,113,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1267,113,'term_description','Riverbench Vineyard was established in 1973, when the first chardonnay and pinot noir grapes were planted on the bank of the Sisquoc River, known as the Santa Maria Bench. For decades since then, some of the most renowned wineries in Santa Barbara have purchased this fruit for their wines. In 2004, Riverbench began producing its own wines in limited quantities, with many available exclusively through tasting rooms in Santa Maria and Santa Barbara, California.  Riverbench is widely considered to be one of the finest producers of sparkling wine in California.'),(1268,113,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1269,113,'term_outbound_url','http://riverbench.com/'),(1270,113,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1271,113,'term_logo','768'),(1272,113,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1273,113,'term_photo',''),(1274,113,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1275,113,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1276,113,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1277,114,'venue_address','627 N. La Peer Drive, West Hollywood, CA 90069'),(1278,114,'_venue_address','field_5a626ef64504f'),(1279,114,'venue_phone','<a href=\"tel://213.296.3038\">213-296-3038</a>'),(1280,114,'_venue_phone','field_5a626f4c45051'),(1281,114,'venue_note','<strong>Getting here</strong>\r\n\r\nWe encourage all attendees to consider using ride-sharing services whenever possible. For those drivning, valet parking is available at the Kimpton La Peer Hotel.'),(1282,114,'_venue_note','field_5a626f5c45052'),(1283,114,'venue_image_a',''),(1284,114,'_venue_image_a','field_5a83bdd4f0958'),(1285,114,'venue_image_b',''),(1286,114,'_venue_image_b','field_5a83bde9f0959'),(1287,115,'term_banner_image',''),(1288,115,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1289,115,'term_lname','Cesarini'),(1290,115,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1291,115,'term_description','Cesarini Sforza has emerged as the most successful example of a company that symbolizes its region, Trentino. Origin, tradition, history and innovation are important elements of its sparkling wines, from the prestigious “Aquila Reale” and the four sophisticated “Tridentvm” wines to its “Brut Riserva,” which has been a consistent favorite for more than forty years.\r\n\r\nEach of these sparkling wines faithfully reflects the region and its winegrowing tradition with strict adherence to a production philosophy that originated many years ago, in 1974, when Count Lamberto Cesarini Sforza and Giuseppe Andreaus founded the domaine in Trento.\r\n\r\nSince then, Cesarini Sforza has always promoted winegrowing that is based on precision and quality, enhancing the value of chardonnay and pinot nero grapes. Over time, the company has been at the heart of projects that have left an important mark on the development and growth of the “Trentino” Classic Method.'),(1292,115,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1293,115,'term_outbound_url','http://www.cesarinisforza.com/en/'),(1294,115,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1295,115,'term_logo','959'),(1296,115,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1297,115,'term_photo',''),(1298,115,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1299,115,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1300,115,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1301,116,'term_banner_image',''),(1302,116,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1303,116,'term_lname','Majolini'),(1304,116,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1305,116,'term_description','The Maiolini family has been connected to wine and grapes since the 15th century. The family traces their roots to Ome, a unique place located on the northeastern border of Franciacorta, Italy\'s famed sparkling wine-producing region. The red grape variety Majolina (recently recognized as a variety indigenous to Lombardy) is a testament to the long history of the family in this region.\r\n\r\nIn 1981 Valentino Maiolini\'s four sons relaunched the Majolini winery. Together they restored the ancient vineyards and built the winery high up on a hill with views that stretch for miles over the village of Ome and the surrounding vineyards. The buildings are crafted from local stone known as Medolo and this pure white limestone is the same component found in the region\'s soil that gives minerality and structure to the Franciacorta wines that are produced here.\r\n\r\nToday the winery is run by Ezio Maiolini and three cousins: Simone, Giovanni, and Elena. For almost twenty years the winemaking process has been shared by Cesari Ferrari from Franciacorta and Jean-Pierre Valade from Champagne, France.'),(1306,116,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1307,116,'term_outbound_url','http://www.majolini.it/en/'),(1308,116,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1309,116,'term_logo','960'),(1310,116,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1311,116,'term_photo',''),(1312,116,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1313,116,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1314,116,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1329,118,'term_banner_image',''),(1330,118,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1331,118,'term_lname','Baron'),(1332,118,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1333,118,'term_description','From the three branches of the Rothschild family sprang an ambition: to achieve great things, as they always have done in their respective fields. To combine the best terroirs with their know-how for a purpose: Barons de Rothschild Champagne.\r\n\r\nDrawing on their experience in the world of wine, the Barons de Rothschild have again achieved excellence. What could be more natural than for them to create a fine wine and for an illustrious newcomer to take its place in the ranks of Champagne? The three branches of the Rothschild family have joined forces with Champagne families whose passion, for generations, has been to produce exceptional wines. This unusual alliance offers every assurance of a fine product, through shared know-how that guarantees top-quality craftsmanship in the purest of traditions. Driven by passion and boldness, the art of inventiveness is a source of achievement. Barons de Rothschild Champagnes celebrate the solemnity and uniqueness of the great moments of success.'),(1334,118,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1335,118,'term_outbound_url','https://www.champagne-bdr.com/en/home/'),(1336,118,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1337,118,'term_logo','961'),(1338,118,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1339,118,'term_photo',''),(1340,118,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1341,118,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1342,118,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1343,119,'term_banner_image',''),(1344,119,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1345,119,'term_lname','Barnaut'),(1346,119,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1347,119,'term_description','Based in Bouzy, this small-estate producer specializes in Pinot Noir-based Champagne. Edmond Barnaut was one of the first to base his brand outside of Reims and Épernay. He set up shop in Bouzy in 1874. Cellars were dug 15 meters underground and five generations of Barnaut descendants have maintained the quality of the house. Production is currently at about 120,000 bottles. The Grande Reserve is 2/3 Pinot Noir and 1/3 Chardonnay, the original blend made by Edmond Barnaut.'),(1348,119,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1349,119,'term_outbound_url','https://www.champagne-barnaut-bouzy.com/english-website/'),(1350,119,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1351,119,'term_logo','1190'),(1352,119,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1353,119,'term_photo',''),(1354,119,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1355,119,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1356,119,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1357,120,'term_banner_image',''),(1358,120,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1359,120,'term_lname','Gonet'),(1360,120,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1361,120,'term_description','Xavier Gonet and his wife Julie Médeville have been working since 2000 on a new Champagne vineyard in Bisseuil, between Mareuil-sur-Ay and Bouzy.  The Champagne Gonet-Médeville is a property of twelve hectares spread over eight villages including three prestigious Grands Crus.'),(1362,120,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1363,120,'term_outbound_url','http://gonet-medeville.com/en/'),(1364,120,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1365,120,'term_logo','962'),(1366,120,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1367,120,'term_photo',''),(1368,120,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1369,120,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1370,120,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1371,121,'term_banner_image',''),(1372,121,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1373,121,'term_lname','Goutorbe'),(1374,121,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1375,121,'term_description','The Goutorbe-Bouillot house is a small estate located in the village of Damery, just west of Épernay. Family-owned and operated since 1911, the 8 hectares of 30 different parcels of vineyards extend over the Vallée de la Marne with a focus on pinot meunier, chardonnay and pinot noir grapes. The marriage of  Jules Goutorbe and Louise Bouillot was the origin of the house with both families’ viticulture practices dating from 1755.\r\n\r\nTrue to the region’s historic emphasis on meunier, the domaine is planted to over 50% of the variety although there is an increasing interest in chardonnay and pinot noir, too.  Goutorbe-Bouillot Champagnes are produced by a method similar to the Solera system in Jerez. Each year they use 50% of this reserve wine in the blend. This means that the wine contains some of all the earlier vintages in decreasing proportions. This perpetual reserve was started in 1980 for the Carte d\'Or and in 2000 for the other non-vintage cuvées. The aim is to give more maturity and complexity to the wines.'),(1376,121,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1377,121,'term_outbound_url','https://www.goutorbe-bouillot.fr/'),(1378,121,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1379,121,'term_logo','963'),(1380,121,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1381,121,'term_photo',''),(1382,121,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1383,121,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1384,121,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1385,122,'term_banner_image',''),(1386,122,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1387,122,'term_lname','Laherte'),(1388,122,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1389,122,'term_description','The Laherte family has a long history in Champagne. Founded in 1889 by Jean-Baptiste Laherte, the estate was originally made up of vines primarily in the village of Chavot. Fourth generation vigneron Michel Laherte expanded the family estate which then covered about five hectares. With his wife Cécile, the two young vignerons modernized the press and tanks, but soon realized that too much modernity such as the use of herbicides and pesticides would prevent full terroir expression in the wines. They began working the soils, gently vinifying the juices, and remaining humble and patient as the wines developed. This philosophy is the foundation of the estate and has endured through the generations.\r\n\r\nToday, under the direction of Aurélien Laherte who took over in 2005, the estate has become one of the most progressive and dynamic \"rising stars\" in the appellation. Like many of Champagne\'s top practitioners, the estate has begun to produce a series of tiny production, single-vineyard/single vintage cuvees (around 3000 bottles each) from some of their most unique and expressive biodynamically-farmed parcels. These wines are all vinified in used Burgundy barrels, without malolactic fermentations, and are bottled without fining and filtration. They are then finished with little or no dosage so as to not mask the individuality of the underlying terroirs'),(1390,122,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1391,122,'term_outbound_url','www.champagne-laherte.com'),(1392,122,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1393,122,'term_logo','1188'),(1394,122,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1395,122,'term_photo',''),(1396,122,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1397,122,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1398,122,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1399,123,'term_banner_image',''),(1400,123,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1401,123,'term_lname','Delamotte'),(1402,123,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1403,123,'term_description','Delamotte is a Champagne house more than 250 years old (it is the fifth oldest Champagne house) founded in Reims in 1760 by François Delamotte, a vineyard owner.  Ownership of the house passed through the Delamotte family then to the Lanson family and finally was bought, along with sister house Champagne Salon, by the Laurent-Perrier group.  The houses have been under the direction of Didier Depond in Le Mesnil-sur-Oger since 1988.  A man of passion and compassion, he is continually developing the outstanding image of these two exceptional wines.  The aesthetic, rigorous endeavour to always work better is a long lasting ideal of the House. One of the founding principles of the House of Delamotte (and of its sister company, Salon) is that Champagne is first and foremost a wine to be enjoyed and appreciated for its quality and authenticity. The wine should be – from the very start – subtle, profound, rich with the aromas and flavors which ultimately create outstanding Champagne.'),(1404,123,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1405,123,'term_outbound_url','http://www.salondelamotte.com/'),(1406,123,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1407,123,'term_logo','571'),(1408,123,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1409,123,'term_photo',''),(1410,123,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1411,123,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1412,123,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1413,124,'term_banner_image',''),(1414,124,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1415,124,'term_lname','Pierre'),(1416,124,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1417,124,'term_description','Located in Mesnil sur Oger, in the heart of the Côte des Blancs, Champagne Pierre Moncuit, a family house and a grower-producer, has based its reputation on a continual search for quality while maintaining its respect for traditions.  Since 1977, Nicole Moncuit, a family scion with both viticultural and oenological credentials, has taken over the technical direction of the house. Now assisted by her brother Yves and her daughter Valérie, the Moncuit family is poised for next-generation success.'),(1418,124,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1419,124,'term_outbound_url','http://www.pierre-moncuit.fr/thehouse.html'),(1420,124,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1421,124,'term_logo','617'),(1422,124,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1423,124,'term_photo',''),(1424,124,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1425,124,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1426,124,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1427,125,'term_banner_image',''),(1428,125,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1429,125,'term_lname','Hébrart'),(1430,125,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1431,125,'term_description','Jean-Paul Hébrart took over the operations of Marc Hébrart Champagne in the Vallée de la Marne from his father Marc in 1997. This estate is not exactly new: Jean-Paul’s father has been producing Champagne under the Marc Hébrart name since 1964 and has been a member of the Special Club since 1985. Hébrart farms 14 hectares of vines on 65 different sites in 6 villages: the 1er cru vineyards of Mareuil-sur-Aÿ, Avenay, Val d’Or and Bisseuil and the grand crus villages of Aÿ as well as Chouilly and Oiry in the Côte des Blancs.'),(1432,125,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1433,125,'term_outbound_url','https://www.skurnik.com/producer/champagne-marc-hebrart/'),(1434,125,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1435,125,'term_logo',''),(1436,125,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1437,125,'term_photo',''),(1438,125,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1439,125,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1440,125,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1441,126,'term_banner_image',''),(1442,126,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1443,126,'term_lname','Heidsieck'),(1444,126,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1445,126,'term_description','Charles Heidsieck is the smallest of the Grandes Marques Champagne Houses. Based in the Reims region of Champagne, it is one of the best-known producers for both vintage and non-vintage cuvées.  It has been part of the luxury EPI group since 2011. The house was founded in 1851 by the French Champagne maker Charles Camille Heidsieck, who later became known as “Champagne Charlie.”\r\n\r\nCharles Heidsieck was born in 1822 into an eminent Reims family whose winemaking traditions date back to Florens-Louis Heidsieck. In 1851, at age 29, he founded a maison bearing his own name. He began to sell his Champagne abroad, starting in Belgium and in England, and in 1852 he travelled to the United States, becoming the first merchant to market his own Champagne there. He was a large- than-life dandy and became something of a social sensation, with one New York newspaper memorably describing him as “Champagne Charlie.” He visited on three further occasions until the American Civil War disrupted trade. He returned to New York in an unsuccessful effort to recover debts owed by his agents and on visiting the south he became trapped by the conflict. In July 1862, Charles Heidsieck was arrested as a spy while travelling to New Orleans trying to flee back to France. He was sent to the infamous Fort Jackson in Louisiana. After many pleas, and the intercession of President Lincoln himself, Charles was released in November 1862, but he returned to France sick and bankrupt. His business was subsequently saved, however, because a debt was repaid in deeds to land in Coronado where, shortly afterwards, there was a silver boom which turned the once obscure village of Denver into a valuable estate.\r\n\r\nCharles Heidsieck focused on selecting, blending and ageing wines to produce higher quality Champagnes, buying grapes from individual growers. In 1867 he purchased several old chalk quarries, called crayères which dated from the Gallo-Roman era, in order to create optimal conditions for wine maturation. There cellars are now inscribed on the UNESCO World Heritage List along with other Champagne vineyards, houses and cellars.'),(1446,126,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1447,126,'term_outbound_url','https://charlesheidsieck.com/en'),(1448,126,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1449,126,'term_logo','1132'),(1450,126,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1451,126,'term_photo',''),(1452,126,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1453,126,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1454,126,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1455,127,'term_banner_image',''),(1456,127,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1457,127,'term_lname','Weingut'),(1458,127,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1459,127,'term_description','The family-owned winery Kirsten is surrounded by the steep slopes and blue-slate soils of the Mosel. Bernhard Kirsten took over in 1992 from his parents. Everything began with the historic vineyards in Klüsserath - of which there is a parcel in the Klüsserather Brotherhood Moselfront. With his ambition and passion, Bernhard Kirsten was able to turn what was a tiny farm into a renowned steep-slope vineyard producing world-class wines.  More than 14 varieties of wine are cultivated in this area, including riesling, pinot blanc, sauvignon blanc, pinot noir and three different types of sparkling wines are produced.'),(1460,127,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1461,127,'term_outbound_url','www.weingut-kirsten.de/'),(1462,127,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1463,127,'term_logo','1200'),(1464,127,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1465,127,'term_photo',''),(1466,127,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1467,127,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1468,127,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1483,129,'term_banner_image',''),(1484,129,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1485,129,'term_lname','Jaume'),(1486,129,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1487,129,'term_description','Jaume Giró i Giró is one of the most historic cellars of Sant Sadurní d´Anoia. It is known for its elegant hand-produced cava made in extremely limited quantities.  The history of this family-owned company goes back to the middle of the XIX Century.  It is currently run by the enologist Ramon Giró Gramón, the third generation of the family and a winemaker who has propelled the house forward in the production and in the overall quality of its wines.  This cava is the embodiment of an artisanal philosophy: high quality and selection of grapes from vintages regarded as excellent, further enhanced by the lateest technologies, allowing them to offer top quality sparkling wines that reflect a unique, creative genius.  This boutique winery offers top quality cavas made using traditional Champagne-influenced techniques.'),(1488,129,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1489,129,'term_outbound_url','http://www.cavagiro.com/en'),(1490,129,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1491,129,'term_logo','1134'),(1492,129,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1493,129,'term_photo',''),(1494,129,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1495,129,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1496,129,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1497,130,'term_banner_image',''),(1498,130,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1499,130,'term_lname','Bodegas'),(1500,130,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1501,130,'term_description','Much like in Champagne, a new wave of growers in Spain’s Catalunya region are reinvigorating “farmer fizz”. Long-considered one of the great treasures of the Peñedès region, the sparkling wines of Bodegas Colet offer both value and nuance. The Colet family, helmed by son Sergi Colet’s winemaking, have been growing grapes since the 1970s although they did not bottle under their own label until 1987.\r\n\r\nDesignated as DO Peñedès since 2004 rather than as Cava, the sparkling wines from this bodega offer exceptional value and quality. <span style=\"display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: transparent; color: #333333; font-family: Georgia,\'Times New Roman\',\'Bitstream Charter\',Times,serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 24px; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; word-wrap: break-word;\">Made from the traditional trio of Catalan grapes, Colet\'s sparklers are a wonderful introduction to Spanish bubblies. </span>'),(1502,130,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1503,130,'term_outbound_url','www.colet.cat/EN/vins.html'),(1504,130,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1505,130,'term_logo','1160'),(1506,130,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1507,130,'term_photo',''),(1508,130,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1509,130,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1510,130,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1511,131,'term_banner_image',''),(1512,131,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1513,131,'term_lname','Hillersden'),(1514,131,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1515,131,'term_description','Hillersden is the home of the first family-owned winery in the Upper Wairau Valley on the edge of Marlborough’s wine growing region in New Zealand. Its mission is to craft wines of character, expressive of both site and vintage, while being responsible caretakers of its land and its people. At the heart of their operation is the marriage of nature and technology to improve upon the quality of the harvest and the livelihood of the grower. Hillersden makes exceptional sparkling sauvignon blanc that is a gorgeous expression of Marlborough fruit.'),(1516,131,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1517,131,'term_outbound_url','https://hillersden.com/'),(1518,131,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1519,131,'term_logo','1136'),(1520,131,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1521,131,'term_photo',''),(1522,131,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1523,131,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1524,131,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1525,132,'term_banner_image',''),(1526,132,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1527,132,'term_lname','Villa'),(1528,132,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1529,132,'term_description','In 1961, at just 21 years of age, George Fistonich leased five acres of land from his father in Mangere, Auckland and started off with just an acre of vines. He harvested his first grapes in 1962 and made his first wine under the name Villa Maria.  Throughout the 1960s Villa Maria was a one-man band, with George’s wife, Gail, supporting him in his venture. He made dry red and white wines, sourcing grapes from the greater Auckland regions. In the early 1970s he started to employ staff and the company began to expand rapidly.  Today, Villa Maria employs more than 250 permanent staff and exports wine to over 50 countries worldwide.  We are pleased to feature their delicious New Zealand bubbly at Effervescence.'),(1530,132,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1531,132,'term_outbound_url','http://www.villamariawine.com/'),(1532,132,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1533,132,'term_logo','1137'),(1534,132,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1535,132,'term_photo',''),(1536,132,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1537,132,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1538,132,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1539,133,'term_banner_image',''),(1540,133,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1541,133,'term_lname','Lilbert'),(1542,133,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1543,133,'term_description','Lilbert owns 3.5 hectare of vines- all Grand Cru, and all Chardonnay, with an average vine age of 45 years- in the Côte des Blancs. 60% of their vines are in Cramant, 30% in Chouilly and 10% in Oiry. These are three of the six Grand Cru villages in the Côte des Blancs.\r\n\r\nIt is rare that any one house owns exclusively Grand Cru vineyards in the Côte des Blancs; Bertrand calls himself \"very lucky\" to be able to make wines from such prestigious vineyards. All of the parcels are vinified separately until two weeks before bottling. The NV represents 80% of the production and is aged in the cellar for two years. Dosage is normally around 7g/L, since Bertrand is going for acidity in his wines and not ripeness. (He does not perform batonnage because it makes the wines too heavy.) The winery is tiny and the latest investment is a 4,000kg pneumatic press and a disgorgement machine. Each bottle is still riddled by hand. The end result is a true connoisseur’s Champagne.'),(1544,133,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1545,133,'term_outbound_url','www.champagne-lilbert.com/'),(1546,133,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1547,133,'term_logo','1161'),(1548,133,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1549,133,'term_photo',''),(1550,133,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1551,133,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1552,133,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1553,134,'term_banner_image',''),(1554,134,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1555,134,'term_lname','Weingut'),(1556,134,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1557,134,'term_description','Founded in 1786 by Jacobus Kühn, The Kühn estate remains a family operated winery currently run by 11th generation winemakers Peter Jakob, his wife Angela, and their son Peter Bernhard. The entirety of their efforts is in the pursuit of exploring the potential of and finding the purest possible expression of, their grapes. Peter Bernhard graduated from the prestigious Geisenheim university after stages in Burgundy and Alsace (at Zind-Humbrecht) and has been working in the estate’s cellars ever since. Having studied thoroughly both the philosophical aspects of biodynamicism and the science of both grape growing and winemaking, Peter Junior lends a fantastic perspective and represents the next generation of Kühn family winemaking.\r\n\r\nThe Kühn family history is intrinsically woven into their land. For over 200 years the Kühns have meticulously maintained their vineyards and developed a deep appreciation of their land, its flora and fauna. The decision to embrace biodynamic principles was borne of this relationship and an earnest desire to produce vibrant, expressive wines that did justice to the terroir on which their family has farmed for 10 generations. As the first (and still the only) biodynamic producer in the Rheingau, the Kühns have fully embraced every aspect of the preparation, the application and the philosophy of biodynamic farming and have quickly become icons for profound Riesling and natural, organic wines.'),(1558,134,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1559,134,'term_outbound_url','http://www.weingutpjkuehn.de/en/home/'),(1560,134,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1561,134,'term_logo','1133'),(1562,134,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1563,134,'term_photo',''),(1564,134,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1565,134,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1566,134,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1567,135,'term_banner_image',''),(1568,135,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1569,135,'term_lname','Vergnon'),(1570,135,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1571,135,'term_description','In the heart of the chalk wonderland that is Le Mesnil-sur-Oger, Didier Vergnon and his son Clement are the 4th and 5th generations to lead this small five hectare estate. Founded in 1950, it was in 1985 that Jean-Louis Vergnon first began producing estate-bottled wine from some of their choice sites, including multiple Grand Cru parcels in and next to the legendary Les Chetillons.\r\n\r\nOver the last fifteen years this family property has truly emerged as one of the elite properties in the Côte des Blancs. It was in the early 1980’s that Didier’s father had the foresight and began the push to harvest only balanced and ripe grapes, with up to 11 degrees of natural potential alcohol or more. This allowed the family to completely eliminate chaptalization, block malolactic fermentation, and use a generally very low dosage across the range. Most of the wines are vinified in stainless steel tanks and aged for a minimum of thirty-six months on the lees, with most aging for much longer before release.'),(1572,135,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1573,135,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagne-jl-vergnon.com/presentation-en.html'),(1574,135,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1575,135,'term_logo','1191'),(1576,135,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1577,135,'term_photo',''),(1578,135,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1579,135,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1580,135,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1581,136,'venue_address','5722 Melrose Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90038'),(1582,136,'_venue_address','field_5a626ef64504f'),(1583,136,'venue_phone','<a href=\"tel://323.871.4160\">323-871-4160</a>'),(1584,136,'_venue_phone','field_5a626f4c45051'),(1585,136,'venue_note','We encourage all guests to use car services whenever possible. If driving, there is valet parking available at the restaurant.'),(1586,136,'_venue_note','field_5a626f5c45052'),(1587,136,'venue_image_a','1591'),(1588,136,'_venue_image_a','field_5a83bdd4f0958'),(1589,136,'venue_image_b','569'),(1590,136,'_venue_image_b','field_5a83bde9f0959'),(1591,137,'term_banner_image',''),(1592,137,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1593,137,'term_lname','Flying'),(1594,137,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1595,137,'term_description','Flying Goat Cellars is the original sparkling wine producer in Santa Barbara County. In 2005, winemaker Norm Yost launched the production of a sparkling wine program under the Goat Bubbles brand using the méthode champenoise technique.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2068\" src=\"https://effervescencela.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Flying-Goats-SO1091639-3_p1_FGC_13BlancDeNoirsft.jpg\" alt=\"Goat Bubbles logo\" width=\"563\" height=\"563\" />\r\n\r\nFlying Goat Cellars is handcrafting sparkling wine at its own facility in Lompoc, CA, where every step of the process is done in-house. The winery now produces five distinct sparkling wines, Crémant, Blanc de Blancs, Blanc de Noirs, Brut Cuvée and Rosé. All of the wines are limited production, single vineyard and low dosage of less than 7 g/L'),(1596,137,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1597,137,'term_outbound_url','http://www.flyinggoatcellars.com'),(1598,137,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1599,137,'term_logo','1536'),(1600,137,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1601,137,'term_photo',''),(1602,137,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1603,137,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1604,137,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1605,138,'term_banner_image',''),(1606,138,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1607,138,'term_lname','Ca'),(1608,138,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1609,138,'term_description','There are moments without words that only sensations can define, feelings that reach the heart and become the rapture, joy and beauty of a moment to be treasured deep inside. The art of wine is one such moment, a masterpiece created by the talent that few possess, in which dedication and ability blend in a magical, mystical marriage with nature. The infinite in a single drop, fruit of a slow, devoted and meticulous passion. People, like territories, have a vocation. And so it was that a fifteen-year-old boy had a lightning intuition of what life could be like pursuing it.\r\n\r\nThe meeting between young Maurizio Zanella and gentle Franciacorta, when his mother moved to Erbusco and planted the first vineyard, was the initial contact with what would be the love of his life. But it was after a trip to Champagne, to the famous maisons whose wine had always fascinated and inspired him, that Maurizio returned with the unshakable idea of making something similar. What was once a house in a chestnut wood became one of the most trailblazing wineries in Italy.\r\n\r\nSince then a single principle has been defining the essence of Ca’del Bosco: the quest for excellence.'),(1610,138,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1611,138,'term_outbound_url','www.cadelbosco.com/en/'),(1612,138,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1613,138,'term_logo','1606'),(1614,138,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1615,138,'term_photo',''),(1616,138,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1617,138,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1618,138,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1643,142,'term_banner_image',''),(1644,142,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1645,142,'term_logo','1608'),(1646,142,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1647,142,'term_lname','Meehan'),(1648,142,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1649,142,'term_organization_name','Kali'),(1650,142,'_term_organization_name','field_5a696b2b7a980'),(1651,142,'term_outbound_url','https://www.kalirestaurant.com/'),(1652,142,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1653,142,'term_description','With the opening of Kali Restaurant, Chef Kevin Meehan\'s broad 23-year culinary career reaches its apex. At Kali, Meehan, whose deft hand was cultivated in Los Angeles\' most prestigious kitchens, joins forces with long-time friend and professional colleague, Drew Langley, previously the wine director at the iconic, Michelin-starred Providence.\r\n\r\nFor the 39-year-old Meehan, Kali represents the evolution of not just Kali Dining, his roving private dinner pop-up, but the rigorous years he spent refining his craft. The contemporary California restaurant blends the precision and hospitality of the white tablecloth kitchens where Meehan developed his culinary acumen, with the accessibility and ease of a local\'s favorite neighborhood haunt.\r\n\r\nIn 2012, Meehan launched his passion project, Kali Dining. The underground operation quickly garnered critical attention for Meehan\'s assertive, yet nuanced tasting menus that he prepared, dinner party-style, for Los Angeles top tastemakers, luminaries, and food enthusiasts. Kali the restaurant was birthed from the success of Kali Dining, and the passion that Meehan and co-owner Langley share for pushing the boundaries of the typical fine dining experience.'),(1654,142,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1655,142,'term_photo','1607'),(1656,142,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1657,142,'participants_clone_term_meta',''),(1658,142,'_participants_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fd4fc5562'),(1659,143,'term_banner_image',''),(1660,143,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1661,143,'term_lname','Carneros'),(1662,143,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1663,143,'term_description','Domaine Carneros is a singular winery best known as a small grower-producer of methóde traditionnelle sparkling wine, pinot noir, estate vineyards, and a breathtakingly beautiful château. Founded by the noble family behind Champagne Taittinger, Claude Taittinger\'s search for a worthy U.S. counterpart began in the late 1970s. In 1987 he selected a 138-acre parcel in the heart of Carneros, Napa Valley. Wisely selecting Eileen Crane to oversee the development of the winery and vineyards, the team created the quintessential California expression of the Taittinger style in Carneros.'),(1664,143,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1665,143,'term_outbound_url','https://www.domainecarneros.com/'),(1666,143,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1667,143,'term_logo','1698'),(1668,143,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1669,143,'term_photo',''),(1670,143,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1671,143,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1672,143,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1673,144,'term_banner_image',''),(1674,144,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1675,144,'term_lname','L\'Ormarins'),(1676,144,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1677,144,'term_description','L\'Ormarins the main estate in the Anthonij Rupert Wyne portfolio is situated in the Franschhoek area in South Africa. The farm has a combination of both low-lying land and moderate-to-steep slopes. There is an altitude difference of 385m between the lowest (165m) and the highest (580m) points on the farm.\r\n\r\nThe vineyards are mainly planted on the slopes of the Groot Drakenstein mountains where granite soils produce robust, expressive wines.\r\n\r\nIn 2011 the property situated to the east of L\'Ormarins -which belonged to Graham Beck was purchased and now forms part of the L\'Ormarins vineyards. Most of the existing vines were uprooted and only the Chardonnay and Pinot Noir blocks were left, as these grapes will be used for the L\'Ormarins Méthode Cap Classique wines.'),(1678,144,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1679,144,'term_outbound_url','https://www.rupertwines.com/farms.php?farms_id=1'),(1680,144,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1681,144,'term_logo','1731'),(1682,144,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1683,144,'term_photo',''),(1684,144,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1685,144,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1686,144,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1687,145,'term_banner_image',''),(1688,145,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1689,145,'term_lname','graham'),(1690,145,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1691,145,'term_description','From grape to glass the time honored process of creating a world class Méthode Cap Classique relies on meticulous attention to detail, dedication to authenticity, precision timing and plenty of patience.\r\n\r\nThe prestigious Graham Beck Cap Classique Portfolio from South Africa consists of three ranges: the Non Vintage Collection (Brut Non Vintage, Brut Rosé Non Vintage and Bliss Demi Sec Non Vintage), the Vintage Collection (Blanc de Blancs, Brut Rosé and Brut Zero) and the Prestige Collection (Cuvée Clive). Each exquisitely crafted wine is unique in both its style and individual characteristics, whilst all of these celebrated sparkling wines epitomize the elegance, sophistication, timelessness and superb quality Graham Beck has become renowned for. These seven Méthode Cap Classique’s also embody the rewarding versatility and extensive appeal of the portfolio – with a bubbly to complement every moment, mood, dish and desire.'),(1692,145,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1693,145,'term_outbound_url','www.grahambeckwines.co.za/'),(1694,145,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1695,145,'term_logo','1732'),(1696,145,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1697,145,'term_photo',''),(1698,145,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1699,145,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1700,145,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1701,146,'term_banner_image',''),(1702,146,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1703,146,'term_lname','boschendal'),(1704,146,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1705,146,'term_description','Given its exceptional winemaking heritage of almost 300 years, the Boschendal cellar masters meticulously balance rustic tradition and modern innovation to produce classic, fruity wines while upholding the ecological integrity that has become synonymous with their brand.\r\n\r\nEach wine range, including chardonnay, sauvignon blanc, cabernet sauvignon, merlot and shiraz, is carefully crafted to deliver ultimate drinking pleasure, with dedicated red and white winemakers in separate cellars for focused expertise. It is this attention to detail that makes us a leader in the production of Méthode Cap Classique sparkling wines and beloved brand in over 50 countries.'),(1706,146,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1707,146,'term_outbound_url','https://www.boschendalwines.com/'),(1708,146,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1709,146,'term_logo','1733'),(1710,146,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1711,146,'term_photo',''),(1712,146,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1713,146,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1714,146,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1715,147,'term_banner_image',''),(1716,147,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1717,147,'term_lname','backsberg'),(1718,147,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1719,147,'term_description','The philosophy of Backsberg remains that of providing pleasure and enjoyment to a broad range of wine lovers by producing wines not only with structure and finesse, but also with a high level of “drinkability.”\r\n\r\nThe Kosher wines are made under the auspices of the Cape Town Beth Din and the OU of the United States. The wines are Mevushal and Kosher for Passover.'),(1720,147,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1721,147,'term_outbound_url','http://backsberg.co.za/product-category/wine-range/kosher-wines/'),(1722,147,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1723,147,'term_logo','1734'),(1724,147,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1725,147,'term_photo',''),(1726,147,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1727,147,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1728,147,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1729,148,'term_banner_image',''),(1730,148,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1731,148,'term_lname','simonsig'),(1732,148,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1733,148,'term_description','Frans Malan, the founder of Simonsig, was the first producer of Méthode Champenoise in South Africa, when he pioneered Cap Classique in 1971.  Legions of fellow South African producers of sparkling wine have followed suit, but Simonsig remains the standard-bearer for quality sparkling wine in the area.'),(1734,148,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1735,148,'term_outbound_url','http://www.simonsig.co.za/'),(1736,148,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1737,148,'term_logo','1709'),(1738,148,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1739,148,'term_photo',''),(1740,148,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1741,148,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1742,148,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1743,149,'term_banner_image',''),(1744,149,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1745,149,'term_lname','Bruno'),(1746,149,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1747,149,'term_description','Maison Bruno Paillard sprang from its founder’s desire to create a Champagne different from any other – one that is extremely pure.\r\n\r\nA great Champagne for Bruno Paillard is – above all – an “assemblage” blending: of diverse crus, grape varieties and vintages. It is about the constant desire to capture the quintessential finesse and elegance which Champagne can bring when it is served with love and care.\r\n\r\nThe Bruno Paillard style is a marriage of elegance and complexity which is manifested as a light and smooth effervescence, a remarkable purity, a true freshness and a silky texture.\r\n\r\nThe effervescence must be delicate. The bubbles are very tiny, almost microscopic, yet they are what release the wine’s aromas and give it a smooth and creamy texture on the palate.\r\n\r\nComplexity must not be confused with heaviness; rather, it is more about elegance. The balance and the depth of the wines are what gives them their purity. Complexity only reveals itself to those who take time to discover, emerging as the wines age.'),(1748,149,'_term_description','field_5a68eea623c97'),(1749,149,'term_outbound_url','http://www.champagnebrunopaillard.com/en/'),(1750,149,'_term_outbound_url','field_5a68cda3135c9'),(1751,149,'term_logo','1704'),(1752,149,'_term_logo','field_5a68eda7a5824'),(1753,149,'term_photo',''),(1754,149,'_term_photo','field_5a68fba28eade'),(1755,149,'producers_clone_term_meta',''),(1756,149,'_producers_clone_term_meta','field_5a68fdaed90df'),(1757,150,'term_banner_image',''),(1758,150,'_term_banner_image','field_5a85c6b7cac4a'),(1759,150,'term_lname','Longridge'),(1760,150,'_term_lname','field_5a68f2ed46aa0'),(1761,150,'term_description','Longridge Wine Estate, one of the leading wine estates in South Africa, is situated in the Stellenbosch region on the slopes of the Helderberg mountain range. The farm was first registered in 1841 and underwent a few name changes before finally being called Longridge in 1992, when commercial wine production first started.  As winemaker Jasper Raats says, “Our goal is to produce world class wines in a natural way, applying the age-old traditions of natural winemaking and respecting our land,